'''Amy B. Jordan''' (born November 23, 1961) is Associate Dean for Undergraduate Studies at the Annenberg School for Communication of the University of Pennsylvania.  Her research and teaching focuses on the role of media in the lives of children and their families and the potential for communication messages to address health risk behaviors.

Amy Jordan received her M.A. (1986) and PhD. (1990) from the [[Annenberg School for Communication at the University of Pennsylvania|Annenberg School for Communication]], and graduated [[summa cum laude]] and [[Phi Beta Kappa]] from [[Muhlenberg College]] in 1983 with a B.A. in Communication Studies.

