There are hundreds of lakes in the [[Sawtooth Range (Idaho)|Sawtooth Mountains]], most of which have been created by alpine glaciers.  The majority of the lakes are within the [[Sawtooth Wilderness]], but several are not yet still within [[Sawtooth National Recreation Area]] The largest lakes are Redfish, Alturas, Pettit, Yellow Belly, Stanley, and Sawtooth lakes.<ref>Sawtooth National Forest. "Sawtooth National Forest" [map].1:126,720, 1"=2 miles. Twin Falls, Idaho: Sawtooth National Forest, United States Forest Service, 1998.</ref>

