''' Olivier Doré''' is a cosmologist, who is currently working as research scientist in [[Jet Propulsion Laboratory]] and visiting associate faculty at the [[California Institute of Technology]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://science.jpl.nasa.gov/people/ODore/ |title=Origin of the Universe (3268): People |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=<!--Not stated--> |website=/science.jpl.nasa.gov |publisher=[[Jet Propulsion Laboratory]] |access-date= 8 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cita.utoronto.ca/~olivier/Olivier_Dore_home_page/Home.html |title=Olivier Doré |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=<!--Not stated--> |website=cita.utoronto.ca |publisher=[[University of Toronto]] |access-date= 8 December 2017}}</ref>
==Awards== * [[Breakthrough Prize in Fundamental Physics]], December 2017<ref>{{cite web |url=https://science.gsfc.nasa.gov/sed/index.cfm?fuseAction=home.main&&navOrgCode=660 |title=Congratulations to Charles Bennett, Gary Hinshaw, Norman Jarosik, Lyman Page Jr., David Spergel and the WMAP Science Team for winning the 2018 Breakthrough Prize in Fundamental Physics |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=3 December 2017 |website=science.gsfc.nasa.gov |publisher=[[NASA]] |access-date=8 December 2017}}</ref> * UC Irvine, Distinguished Visiting Professor, 2017, date * Laboratoire d’Astrophysique de Marseille (LAM), Aix-Marseille Universit´e, France, Visiting Professor, 2017, 1 month * JPL Voyager award, May 2016 * [[Jet Propulsion Laboratory|JPL]] Team award for outstanding contribution to the SPHEREx Proposal Team, February 2015 * [[Jet Propulsion Laboratory|JPL]] Mariner award, May 2013 * Gruber 2012 Cosmology Prize awarded to Charles Bennett and the WMAP team * [[NASA]] Group Achievement Award (as a member of the NASA [[Planck (spacecraft)|Planck satellite]] science team), May 2009, May 2010, September 2014 * [[NASA]] Group Achievement Award (as a member of the NASA [[Wilkinson Microwave Anisotropy Probe|WMAP satellite]] science team), May 2007 * Fellow of the Société de secours des amis des sciences,
